Bill Nye 'the Science Guy' joined President Barack Obama on Air Force One for his Earth Day trip to the Florida Everglades . 
  Nye held court with press before boarding the plane and told them he loves the smell of jet fuel . 
  The president flew nearly 2,000 miles round-trip to the swamp and back . 
  Obama used the trip to promote his administration's commitment to cutting carbon pollution . 
  The White House said Tuesday that Nye would make the trek to shoot a video of the president . 
 